recv returns 0 or -1 in case of client disconnected , look for each one of them when it is returned
there is c++ networking stl standard library for network programmin but is is only available on c++20
there is no guarantee that recv returns null terminated string, so this will be handled by the number of bits recieved
if you dident close the socket the client will remain waiting for data until it times out
[inetd] a service on linux and mac os turn console-only application to network once, look for it for more details
